race.description: Markey Saddlery Reg & Rose Paine Memorial Handicap
race.comment: TANGO ON (10) won well two back from on the speed before striking a good CL1 at Nowra last time out where he was well beaten. Lever taking over from the apprentice hoop is a big push for his chances. This looks an easier race on paper and he can make his presence felt. BOLO MISS (5) showed plenty of ability in her debut campaign, winning as an odds-on favourite two back before a strong effort before the break. She'll be fitter for a trial at Queanbeyan a month ago and Cahill's record at this course is phenomenal. Looks the main danger. KEV'S GIRL (1) strikes a suitable race today despite tiring from the front at Canberra last time out. Ramsbotham is in form and she's not to be discounted. GIZA (7) can make a statement on debut.
